OL,3,CSobriety and alcohol deaths on the
OL,4,Crise - can the UK ditch booze?
OL,6,FWords by Toby Winson
OL,8,FAlcohol is number one on the guest
OL,9,Flist to almost every event in the UK `
OL,10,Fwhether that's a birthday party,
OL,11,Fwedding, or wake. It's ingrained in
OL,12,Four culture.
OL,14,FBut the relationship we have with
OL,15,Fdrink is changing. Around a quarter of
OL,16,Fyoung people are choosing to ditch
OL,17,Fbooze all together, the low and no
OL,18,Falcohol industry is booming and
OL,19,FAlcohol Change UK estimate millions of
OL,20,FBrits are participating in Dry January
OL,21,Fthis year.
