OL,3,CSobriety and alcohol deaths on the
OL,4,Crise - can the UK ditch booze?
OL,6,FAt my worst, I was drinking a litre
OL,7,Fand a half of vodka a day or the
OL,8,Fequivalent in cheap, battery-acid-like
OL,9,Fcider. My days would consist of
OL,10,Fthrowing up blood and bile and trying
OL,11,Fto get enough alcohol to keep the
OL,12,Fwithdrawals at bay. I was terrified of
OL,13,Fhaving another seizure or, even worse,
OL,14,Fan onslaught of hallucinations.
OL,16,FThe thing that I initially thought was
OL,17,Fmy saviour, ended up ripping my life
OL,18,Fto pieces. It consumed what were
OL,19,Fsupposed to be the best years of my
OL,20,Flife and made me feel like I was
OL,21,Fworthless.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/33
