OL,6,FI spent a month in King's College
OL,7,FHospital where the incredible doctors
OL,8,Fand nurses saved my life. But I was
OL,9,Ftold that the scarring to my liver was
OL,10,Fthere for good. That meant that even
OL,11,Fif I stopped drinking completely, I
OL,12,Fwas at greater risk of developing
OL,13,Fserious conditions such as liver
OL,14,Fcancer.
OL,16,FFortunately, my story has a happy
OL,17,Fending and one that can offer some
OL,18,Fhope. Eight years ago, I got sober for
OL,19,Fgood. I realised that I wasn't
OL,20,Fworthless and that I had an illness.
