OL,6,FI worked out what worked for me:
OL,7,Fexercise, setting small goals, a
OL,8,Fhealthy routine and most importantly,
OL,9,Ftalking about my alcoholism and
OL,10,Frecovery at every opportunity.
OL,12,FI realised that bottling up my
OL,13,Fthoughts and feelings was the thing
OL,14,Fthat kept bringing me down. I'm one of
OL,15,Fthe lucky ones who managed to break
OL,16,Ffree from alcohol addiction. Sobriety
OL,17,Fis not a choice for me, it's a
OL,18,Fnecessity for my survival.
