OL,6,FElla, the society's treasurer, said:
OL,7,F"Young people are becoming a lot more
OL,8,Faware of the dangers of drinking. I
OL,9,Fthink for me, for women at least,
OL,10,Fthere is that safety element. You do
OL,11,Fall you can to kind of make yourself
OL,12,Fless vulnerable to any potential
OL,13,Fcrime".
OL,15,FJoey, the president of the society,
OL,16,Fsays heavy drinking used to affect his
OL,17,Fstudies and relationships. He says
OL,18,Fjoining a group of likeminded people
OL,19,Fhas helped him since he gave up
OL,20,Falcohol.
