OL,3,CSobriety and alcohol deaths on the
OL,4,Crise - can the UK ditch booze?
OL,6,FJohn Holmes, Professor of Alcohol
OL,7,FPolicy at the University of Sheffield,
OL,8,Fhas been leading a study on the impact
OL,9,Fof no and low drinks on the UK.
OL,11,FHe said: "It's very clear that people
OL,12,Ffrom more advantaged backgrounds,
OL,13,Fpeople with higher incomes, people in
OL,14,Fmore professional jobs are more likely
OL,15,Fto consume no and low alcohol drinks
OL,16,Fand more likely to do so more
OL,17,Ffrequently as well. We don't at the
OL,18,Fmoment know the full reasons for that.
OL,19,FIt's likely that price is playing a
OL,20,Frole."
