OL,3,CSobriety and alcohol deaths on the
OL,4,Crise - can the UK ditch booze?
OL,6,FThe record number of alcohol deaths
OL,7,Fhave widely been attributed to a huge
OL,8,Fincrease in harmful drinking during
OL,9,Fthe pandemic. No-one knows how long
OL,10,Fthat impact will be felt. Dr Ryan
OL,11,FBuchanan, a Hepatologist at
OL,12,FSouthampton General hospital, says the
OL,13,Flag is ongoing:
OL,15,F"Liver wards here and around the
OL,16,Fcountry have middle aged people,
OL,17,Fforties, 50-year-olds dying in
OL,18,Fnumbers. And if you look around a
OL,19,Fhospital, generally speaking, the only
OL,20,Fother ward where that's happening is
OL,21,Fthe cancer care ward."
