OL,3,CSobriety and alcohol deaths on the
OL,4,Crise - can the UK ditch booze?
OL,6,FDr Buchanan says that although he
OL,7,Ffinds "the sober movement in the
OL,8,Fcountry encouraging", he is cautious
OL,9,Fabout the impact it will have on his
OL,10,Fward.
OL,12,F"My slight concern about it is ` who
OL,13,Fis participating in sobriety?
OL,14,FOverwhelmingly, we see patients dying
OL,15,Fof liver disease who are from some of
OL,16,Four most marginalized and
OL,17,Fsocioeconomically deprived
OL,18,Fpopulations," he said.
